fields.Title: You: ""Huh?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Huh?"

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Not Dora *Du Bois*?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Not Dora *Du Bois*?

fields.Dialogue Text: "He meant *join* us. At Precinct 41. Transfer."

fields.Title: You: ""Yeah. Sure.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah. Sure."

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Tabernacle? It's on the way over...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Tabernacle? It's on the way over. Near where you live, on Perdition..." She looks at Vicquemare.

fields.Title: You: "Not now."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not now.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Under the night sky the great distr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Under the night sky the great district sleeps: A black chessboard of old wooden houses, 80,000 living souls inside. Firetraps as far as the eye can see -- from Main Street to Precinct 41 atop the motorway, to Boogie Street forking into the darkened horizon...

fields.Title: Shivers: "Under the afternoon sky the great d..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Under the afternoon sky the great district hums: A chessboard of wooden houses, 80,000 living souls and chimney stacks. Firetraps as far as the eye can see -- from Main Street to Precinct 41. To Boogie Street forking into the snowswept horizon...

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""You can't be a cop. You're a child..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You can't be a cop. You're a child. And you say 'f****t' every four seconds."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""I don't care -- he can't be a cop...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't care -- he can't be a cop. He's just a kid. A kid who says 'f****t' every four seconds."

fields.Title: You: "The collection of FALN sportswear I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The collection of FALN sportswear I've amassed...

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "For the planetary proletariat."
fields.Dialogue Text: For the planetary proletariat.

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""You manipulative son of a bitch......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "You manipulative son of a bitch..." He shakes his head and sniffles. "It *is* cold, and we have vehicles in the square. The perp needs to be taken into custody. Let's get a move on."

fields.Title: You: ""Why am I *like* this?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why am I *like* this?"

fields.Title: You: ""When was this? When was I a gym te..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When was this? When was I a gym teacher?"

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Couron is just east of Jamrock. It..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Couron is just east of Jamrock. It was a short walk, every morning -- to the baseball field or the sports building...

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno fucking *knew* there had to b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno fucking *knew* there had to be something wrong if you can run like that..."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""You've been on about Mike again?"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You've been on about Mike again?" The detective shakes his head. "I hate that guy."

fields.Title: You: ""I've heard enough." (End it.)"
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've heard enough." (End it.)

fields.Title: You: ""Torson and McLaine?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Torson and McLaine?"

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Us? We're the *Bloody Murder Stati..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Us? We're the *Bloody Murder Station*, haven't you heard? We're the bad guys. No one likes us."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Thank you, Cuno," he says with an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, Cuno," he says with an amused half-smile. "You're being kind. It's an understaffed station and the district is too big -- which is why we need to..." He tilts his head northward and clicks his tongue.

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""And we also have a huge case load,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "And we also have a huge case load, lieutenant," she says with a smile. "Piles that we need to get back to. Mountains, even."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "She lives at 1113 Tabernacle Road,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She lives at 1113 Tabernacle Road, in Jamrock. Remember?

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Detective Kuuno de Ruyter."
fields.Dialogue Text: Detective Kuuno de Ruyter.

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Fuck it, let's go." The man points..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck it, let's go." The man points down the street. "Trant brought his motor carriage. It's a 20 minute drive to Jamrock."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Under the pink morning sky the grea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Under the pink morning sky the great district wakes: A chessboard of wooden houses, 80,000 living souls and chimney stacks. Firetraps as far as the eye can see -- from Main Street to Precinct 41, to Boogie Street forking into the snowswept horizon...

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Look..." She turns to face the sea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look..." She turns to face the sea. "It's raining. It's time to go home."

fields.Title: Shivers: "Under the violet morning sky the gr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Under the violet morning sky the great district wakes: A chessboard of wooden houses, 80,000 living souls and chimney stacks. Firetraps as far as the eye can see -- from Main Street to Precinct 41. To Boogie Street forking into the rainswept horizon...

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Detective." She looks at Vicquemar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Detective." She looks at Vicquemare. "I just don't want this *trial* to go on any longer. It's cold outside, and..."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""No. We're done, Harry. You're drun..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. We're done, Harry. You're drunk. You'll get a station call once you've sobered up."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "No one knows what to say. But they..."
fields.Dialogue Text: No one knows what to say. But they agree. Keeping you on the force endangers civilians.

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Okay." He sighs. "We have vehicles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay." He sighs. "We have vehicles in the square. And the perpetrator needs to be taken into custody. Let's go."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""I don't *want* to. But you discove..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't *want* to. But you discovered a new species. And solved the murder..." He shrugs.

fields.Title: You: ""Who *am* I?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who *am* I?"

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Who *are* you? You're a gym teache..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who *are* you? You're a gym teacher, Harry."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""No," he remarks dryly, "a regular..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No," he remarks dryly, "a regular one."

fields.Title: You: ""How I can keep going for *twelve h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How I can keep going for *twelve hours* a day..."

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Look..." She turns to face the sea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look..." She turns to face the sea. "The sun is about to go down. It's time to go home."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Heartbreak Welkin."
fields.Dialogue Text: Heartbreak Welkin.

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Mack 'The Torso' Torson and Cheste..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mack 'The Torso' Torson and Chester McLaine --" She arches an eyebrow. "They're not fit to run a wing. Believe me. Things are shaky as it is."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Le Retour..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Le Retour...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Perhaps..." He pauses, deep in tho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Perhaps..." He pauses, deep in thought. "There are people who say the Zone of Control will not hold up long. They're not on the radio -- yet. But there are parties out there..."
fields.Alternate1: "Perhaps..." He watches the scrap of newspaper hit the ground. "There are people who say the Zone of Control will not hold up long. They're not on the radio -- yet. But there are parties out there..."

fields.Title: You: ""Jean. I want Cuno at our station,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Jean. I want Cuno at our station, solving this shit."

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Cuno's fuckin' nineteen.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno's fuckin' nineteen."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Wonderful," the woman looks north. "Then can we please just go back to Jamrock now?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "There's an enormous sadness in that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's an enormous sadness in that admission.

fields.Dialogue Text: He nods. "He's too old. He's been like this for too long. I've seen him try many times. It's a farce by now."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "The houses, the streets, the motorw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The houses, the streets, the motorways singing. Hold on. This is a fight we can *win*.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Listen to this shit, man..." He th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen to this shit, man..." He throws up his hands.

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Fucking Harry... Fuck you for brin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fucking Harry... Fuck you for bringing this kid with you. It's *only* because he's defending you -- it's the *only* reason you're not staying here to die."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait. I have a *few* questions bef..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait. I have a *few* questions before we go. About who I am."

fields.Title: You: ""The phasmid -- I need to tell Lena..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The phasmid -- I need to tell Lena about this ASAP."

fields.Title: You: ""Cuno -- what will you do now?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Cuno -- what will you do now?"

fields.Title: You: ""Good bye then. I'll just become a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good bye then. I'll just become a bum now. A bum cop."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""About who you *are*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "About who you *are*?"

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Well -- obviously you're not a gym..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well -- obviously you're not a gym teacher anymore, but..."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""No one is married anymore. This is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No one is married anymore. This is Revachol."

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Pain Welkin."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pain Welkin.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Vaasa is where beautiful and imposs..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Vaasa is where beautiful and impossibly blonde people come from.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you, lieutenant. You're being kind. It *is* an understaffed station and the district *is* too big -- which is why we need to..." He tilts his head northward...

fields.Title: Endurance: "Watch out or she'll faint."
fields.Dialogue Text: Watch out or she'll faint.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""Hey, f****t! You don't get it. Cun..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey, f****t! You don't get it. Cuno's got pig all over him -- Cuno smells of bacon grease. Been *seen* with you. Fuckin' informant shit. You think no one *sees* this?" He spreads his arms.

fields.Title: Cuno: ""I won't say it! I won't say it any..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I won't say it! I won't say it anymore."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""He can't be a cop, Harry. He's a c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He can't be a cop, Harry. He's a child. A child who says 'f****t' every four seconds."

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "It explains everything. All the run..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It explains everything. All the running around. The jumping. The *bicep girth*.

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Okay, so he's stayed clear for wha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, so he's stayed clear for what? A week?" He sighs.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "For Revachol."
fields.Dialogue Text: For Revachol.

fields.Title: You: ""I know it's difficult to believe,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For the white banner of the Commune."
fields.Alternate1: "I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For the Kingdom."
fields.Alternate2: "I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For myself. For *my* life."
fields.Alternate3: "I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For the RCM."

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""Anything that ends the *trial* is..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anything that ends the *trial* is okay with me." A quick nod.

fields.Title: You: ""But before...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "But before..."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""He's been on about Mike again?" Th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's been on about Mike again?" The detective shakes his head. "I hate that guy."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""The regular -- you found some chic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The regular -- you found some chick. She inspired you to fight the *big fight*. Be more than you are. All that."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""My point is, you need to see a *ps..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "My point is, you need to see a *psychiatrist* about this shit. Not a psychologist -- several degrees harder. Is there's something harder than a psychiatrist?" He pauses to think. "A forensic psychiatrist. Go talk to that."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Extremely fuckable, Harry. Gorgeou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Extremely fuckable, Harry. Gorgeous. A gorgeous bourgeois woman. Waifish. Like a *welkin* basically."

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""He's telling the truth. You were a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's telling the truth. You were a gym teacher in Couron." She looks around. "It's getting really cold outside. Should we maybe..."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Detective, we just stopped a small..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Detective, we just stopped a small-scale war. Something is happening to Revachol." He pulls up his collar and looks around, the cold spring light reflected in the lenses of his glasses.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I don't know what, yet -- but it's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know what, yet -- but it's going to be a hard spring for the RCM. We need to get ready. Infiltrate. Investigate."

fields.Title: Drama: "I'm quite sure it wasn't like that,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm quite sure it wasn't like that, sire.

fields.Title: You: ""His dad's in a coma and his only f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "His dad's in a coma and his only friend is gone."

fields.Title: Volition: "Six years and you haven't gotten ov..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Six years and you haven't gotten over it, what the hell is wrong with you?

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "For revenge."
fields.Dialogue Text: For revenge.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Stop and you can go to the Burnt Ou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop and you can go to the Burnt Out Quarter. And meet me there -- wafting above the burnt ruins. Like the smell of caramel -- Le Retour is waiting.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Agreed. The public relations potential of this is too valuable to let go."

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "But he's been drinking, she thinks...."
fields.Dialogue Text: But he's been drinking, she thinks. This is exactly how he gets out of this every time. It's bad for him, but...

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Oh -- you don't say?" He arches an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh -- you don't say?" He arches an eyebrow. "Does he also *vault an impassible gulf of finance and privilege*?"

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""In your twenties or late twenties...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "In your twenties or late twenties. You've really let yourself go since then." He looks you over.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Your love of *retro-style* dance m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Your love of *retro-style* dance music. How you're able to perform a 360-degree spin-kick..."

fields.Title: You: ""No, I meant -- what did she do?""

fields.Dialogue Text: "I assure you -- I wouldn't consult for a corrupt unit."

fields.Dialogue Text: "The press will blow over," he says in a reassuring tone. "Jamrock is lucky to have you. And it's often considered to be the greatest of the districts -- you're lucky to have it."

fields.Title: Judit Minot: ""... get back to it. We left Torson..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "... get back to it. We left Torson and McLaine to run the C-Wing. It's not good."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, you mean The Return?"

fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes." His face darkens. "I hear worries -- from systems analysts in Vesper and Messina. International risks departments in banks. People like that."

fields.Title: Jean Vicquemare: ""Well, you can do that in all the s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, you can do that in all the spare time you're going to have."

fields.Dialogue Text: "He was good. On the island. He can do this."
